title: Our SVP, Your Trend Expert
description: Annie Chen is a self-described fashion-obsessive who has channeled her passion into a career in merchandising, with 15 years in retail as an expert in buying, strategy and design. The opportunity to set a higher standard for the jewelry industry, as well as the chance to bring her expertise to a category she has always loved, is what excites Annie about her role as SVP of Merchandising and Design at Brilliant Earth.

title: 1. Nontraditional Eternity Rings
description: Reflecting a broader cultural push toward creative looks, this trend turns a timeless classic into a more unique choice. Eternity wedding bands feature a continuous circle of diamonds or gemstones that wraps around the entire band, and in 2025, unique stone shapes and creative settings that enhance the overall look are trending. Some couples are opting for oval or emerald-cut stones instead of the traditional round diamonds. Additionally, bezel and flush settings are gaining traction, offering a sleeker, more secure option for those who prefer low-profile designs. Eternity bands make a bold statement, appealing to those who appreciate a bit of sparkle without compromising on classic elegance.
Eternity bands continue to be timeless,
Chen confirms, stating,
Their unbroken circle of stones is a powerful symbol of commitment and love that never fades.

title: 2. Open Rings
description: Cutouts continue to be featured across various aesthetics, from trending fashion to architectural design. Open wedding bands feature a unique gap in the design that adds a contemporary twist. These rings typically have two ends that don't fully meet, creating a sense of openness and allowing for design elements like diamonds or gemstones to be placed on either side of the gap.
Open bands are an innovative twist on the classic wedding ring,
Chen notes.
Their minimal design adds a fresh, contemporary appeal that’s both versatile and chic.

This trend is ideal for individuals who want something different from traditional closed bands and appreciate a modern, minimalistic look. Open bands also work well as stacking rings, making them versatile for those who want to layer their wedding band with engagement rings or other jewelry.

title: 3. Luxe Lab Grown Diamonds
description: Lab-grown diamonds are quickly becoming a preferred choice for sustainable, beautiful jewelry,
says Chen.
They allow couples to embrace ethical luxury without sacrificing quality or style.

With sustainability at the forefront, lab-grown diamonds have become a top choice for wedding bands. Lab-grown diamonds offer the same brilliance and durability as natural diamonds but come with a more affordable price. As couples prioritize ethical choices, wedding bands featuring lab-grown diamonds are emerging in styles that range from classic to modern.

title: 4. Channel Set Rings
description: Overall, trends in fashion are moving towards sleek, practical styles that still make a statement. Channel-set wedding bands exemplify this as a sleek, sophisticated choice that’s also secure. In these designs, small diamonds or gemstones are secured between two metal channels, creating a smooth, streamlined look that keeps the stones flush with the band. This secure setting not only protects the stones from daily wear but also prevents snagging, making it an ideal option for those with active lifestyles. “Channel set bands are especially popular among those who prefer an understated yet luxurious aesthetic, offering just the right amount of elegance and durability,” Chen adds.

title: 5. Curved Rings
description: With a nod toward the arts, we’re seeing sculptural designs take hold in 2025. Curved and contoured wedding bands, designed to sit flush against an engagement ring, create a cohesive, artistic look. This style is particularly popular for individuals with solitaire or unconventional engagement ring shapes, as it accommodates unique designs without leaving a gap.
Curved and contoured bands provide a seamless look when paired with an engagement ring,
Chen observes.
They’re perfect for those who appreciate harmony and balance in their jewelry.

Contoured bands often feature soft curves that enhance the engagement ring, while V-shaped bands offer a contemporary edge. In 2025, more couples are choosing contoured bands with intricate designs or diamond accents, creating a beautiful stacked effect that emphasizes both rings.

title: 6. Textured Rings
description: Classic yet artisanal, textural designs are taking hold of the trends of 2025. Reflecting this, textured wedding bands bring an organic feel and are offered a range of finishes, such as brushed, hammered, and matte textures, each lending a unique flair to the ring. “Textured wedding bands are capturing attention with their unique, artisanal feel,” says Chen. “They are perfect for those seeking a design that stands out subtly, blending craftsmanship with character.” Hammered textures give a rustic, handcrafted appearance. Brushed and matte finishes, on the other hand, create a subtler, low-reflective look that’s perfect for those who prefer a minimalist aesthetic.

title: 7. Men’s Diamond Rings
description: “We’re seeing a growing interest in men’s diamond bands that add a subtle luxury to classic styles,” Chen confirms. “Men are embracing diamonds as part of their wedding jewelry, with designs that range from single accents to more intricate settings, blending masculinity with a touch of sparkle.” Today’s trending wedding rings for men feature diamonds in creative designs, from a single diamond accent inside the band to fully pavé styles, adding a sophisticated sparkle to the classic men’s ring. This trend highlights personalization, allowing men to select diamond wedding bands that align with their individual style.

title: 8. Alternative Metals
description: 2025 trends are shifting towards effortlessly modern looks. Materials like titanium, tungsten, and cobalt offer durability and a fresh, contemporary aesthetic. These metals appeal to couples looking for options beyond traditional gold and platinum, providing a sturdy yet sleek option for those with an active lifestyle.
Alternative metals like titanium and tungsten bring durability with a modern edge,
Chen explains, adding,
These materials offer a sleek, refined look that’s perfect for those seeking something beyond the traditional.
Blackened metals and matte finishes are also gaining popularity, giving wedding bands a bold, understated look that feels fresh and unconventional.
